        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Each sourced exrc file will have its own trust value and the user will have the option to view, trust, or not trust each file in the parent hierarchy.\r\n\r\nCurrently, this PR only loads the first found exrc. Should it keep searching upwards? I think that could actually be helpful, e.g. in your `~/Work/` folder you could set work-specific settings/plugins, while in your `~/Personal` folder, other settings are set. I can change this PR to implement (and document) that behavior.\r\n\r\nEDIT: this PR now executes all exrc files found in parent directories.",
